  <!-- SIGNS YOU NEED A NEW SYSTEM -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your Liverpool Home Needs a Central Heating Upgrade</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Liverpool's housing stock includes a high proportion of older properties that either have no central heating or systems that are significantly underperforming. These are the signs most commonly reported by Liverpool homeowners before they call us.</p>

      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>No central heating at all</strong><p>A significant number of Liverpool's older properties, including converted flats, bedsits and some Victorian terraces, have never had central heating installed. A full system from £3,500 transforms the property completely and adds measurable value.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Rooms that are never warm enough</strong><p>An undersized boiler, poorly balanced system or missing radiators in key rooms means the heating can never keep up. An upgrade or radiator addition resolves this without replacing the whole system in most cases.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>System takes a very long time to warm up</strong><p>A heating system that takes 30 to 45 minutes to reach temperature is losing efficiency. Sludge build-up, a failing pump or an undersized boiler are the most common causes. We diagnose the root cause at the free survey.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Cold spots on radiators</strong><p>Cold at the bottom indicates sludge and magnetite build-up. Cold at the top indicates air in the system. Persistent cold spots after bleeding suggest a power flush is needed before any further work is considered.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Very high heating bills with poor results</strong><p>An inefficient system burning more gas to produce less heat is the most expensive heating problem. A combination of a new A-rated boiler, properly balanced radiators and smart controls typically reduces heating bills by 20 to 35%.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>EPC rating of F or G</strong><p>A poor Energy Performance Certificate rating almost always indicates an inefficient heating system. A new central heating installation is the single biggest improvement available for EPC rating and can add significant property value. See the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/check-energy-performance-certificate" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GOV.UK EPC checker</a>.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1.5rem;text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-size:1rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">Recognise any of these? Book a free no-obligation survey and we will tell you exactly what your Liverpool home needs.</p>
        <a href="tel:07399676656" class="btn btn-lg" style="background:#1a3a5c;color:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(26,58,92,0.4);">CALL 07399 676656</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS INCLUDED -->
