        </div>
        <div class="pf-duration-card">
          <div class="pf-duration-time">3-5<br><span style="font-size:0.9rem;">days</span></div>
          <div><strong>Standard 3 bed property. 7 to 10 radiators.</strong><p>The most common Liverpool installation. Victorian terraces, 1960s semis and 3-bed modern houses across Aigburth, Wavertree, West Derby and Allerton. Includes full system, boiler and smart controls.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-duration-card">
          <div class="pf-duration-time">5-7<br><span style="font-size:0.9rem;">days</span></div>
          <div><strong>Larger property. 11 or more radiators.</strong><p>4 and 5-bed properties in Woolton, Formby, Crosby, Heswall and the wider Merseyside area. More radiators, longer pipe runs and additional complexity. System boiler setup may be required.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-duration-card">
          <div class="pf-duration-time">0.5<br><span style="font-size:0.9rem;">day</span></div>
          <div><strong>Single radiator addition to existing system.</strong><p>Adding one radiator to an existing working central heating system. Pipe connection, balancing and inhibitor top-up included. We can often attend within 2 to 3 days of enquiry.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pf-info-bar" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text);">All timelines are confirmed at the free site survey. Victorian properties with limited floor void access can add 1 to 2 days. We work to a fixed completion schedule agreed at the survey. You are not left waiting for engineers who do not arrive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SMART CONTROLS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Smart Heating Controls for Liverpool Homes</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">A smart thermostat transforms how you control your central heating. Required under Boiler Plus regulations for all new installations and strongly recommended for upgrades.</p>

