      <h2>Power Flushing for Liverpool Heating Systems</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">If you are upgrading an existing system rather than installing new, a power flush before any new components are connected is strongly recommended.</p>

      <div class="pf-card pf-card-orange" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <h3>Why a Power Flush Before a System Upgrade Matters</h3>
        <p>Connecting new radiators, a new boiler or new pipework to a contaminated existing system introduces sludge and magnetite into the new components immediately. This accelerates wear on the new boiler heat exchanger and can cause partial blockages in new radiators within months. All major manufacturers require a clean system as a warranty condition.</p>
        <p>A power flush removes sludge, magnetite and debris from the existing pipework before any new components are connected. This protects your new equipment from day one and is required by Worcester Bosch, Vaillant and all other major manufacturers under their warranty terms. A power flush costs from £350 and is available as a bundle with any system upgrade at a better combined price.</p>
        <p>For full new system installations where all pipework and radiators are new, a power flush is not required. We advise at the free survey whether a power flush is recommended for your specific installation.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:2rem;">
